    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-08T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-08T17:00:00-05:00" n="836"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d836">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.5051/43: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-08T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 8, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>476. RDC and FEA consider it inadvisable to submit to the jurisdiction of the
                    court as suggested in your 652, April 6. Department agrees. You should therefore
                    take matter up with Foreign Office and ask that action be dismissed on the
                    ground that RDC is an official agency of this Government, entirely owned and
                    controlled by the Government, and as such is immune from the jurisdiction of the
                    court. <pb facs="0881" n="867" xml:id="pg_867"/> Its official status has been
                    recognized by the agreement dated July 1, 1942,<note n="40" xml:id="d836fn40"
                        >Text not printed; for correspondence on the negotiation of this agreement,
                        see <ref target="frus1942v06#pg_170">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1942, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">vi</hi>, pp. 170</ref> ff.</note> signed by
                    representatives of our two Governments.</p>
                <p>You may say that if the Colombian Government considers that the plaintiff has a
                    meritorious claim and if such claim is submitted to this Government through the
                    diplomatic channel, it will receive careful consideration.</p>
                <p>Inform representatives RDC and FEA of foregoing. Their principals request that
                    the matter be placed in your hands.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
